Ever wondered what gaming treasures are hiding in Japan? I took a deep dive into Sendico to find out if it's really worth importing retro tech from across the Pacific. From working Xbox 360s with original Blades interface to a $570 Sega Mega Jet that doesn't even work, this haul has some shocking surprises. Is importing from Japan the ultimate gaming goldmine or just an expensive nostalgia trap?
